    <h2>Samsung in LA — Flex Duo dual-oven specialist + Korean mass-market volume</h2>
    <p>Samsung Electronics' residential stove positioning in the US combines mass-market accessibility with feature-density at mid-premium price points. The Flex Duo dual-oven split-cavity design is Samsung's signature differentiator — an internal divider creates two independent temperature zones for simultaneous cooking at different temperatures (e.g., roast lamb at 425°F in upper while pie bakes at 375°F in lower). Air Fry mode uses convection + high temp to replicate air-frying without separate equipment. SmartThings Wi-Fi integration connects Samsung stoves to the broader SmartThings smart-home ecosystem covering Samsung refrigeration + laundry + dishwashers.</p>
    <p>LA service volume distributes similarly to LG Korean-brand geography: Koreatown + Hollywood condo + apartment density (strong Korean-American brand recognition), Valley mass-market (Sherman Oaks, Van Nuys, Northridge, Woodland Hills), South Bay mid-market (Torrance, Long Beach, Redondo Beach), Westside mid-market (Culver City, Mar Vista, Palms), Pasadena + San Gabriel Valley. Bespoke color-panel Samsung stoves are emerging in Westside design-forward kitchens coordinating with Bespoke refrigeration.</p>
